# KOL MVP — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local development:
#     cp .env.example .env.local
#
# `.env.local` is gitignored. Never commit real keys — this file holds
# names and descriptions only, never values.
#
# STATUS: as of this commit the app reads NO environment variables at
# runtime. Every data source is the in-repo mock layer (src/lib/mock).
# The app builds and runs correctly with no .env file at all. The vars
# below are the ones the next build waves will introduce; they are
# listed here so deploy config can be staged ahead of the code.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI — maker interview, voice anchor, store-block critic
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# OPTIONAL — Anthropic API key. Without it the AI surfaces (/sell/interview,
# /sell/voice, the block critic) run in SIMULATED mode: scripted responses
# from the mock layer, no network call, no cost. Set it to exercise the
# real model path. Server-side only — must never be exposed to the client.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Not yet wired — listed so nobody assumes they are configured
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# There is no Supabase, Stripe, Resend, or analytics integration in this
# app yet. When those land (ADR-0001 migration onward) their vars belong
# here with the same REQUIRED/OPTIONAL annotation.
